ly%20four%20out%20of%20ten%20youth%20in%20the%20workforce%20possess%20formal%20skills%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20female%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%20is%20at%2032%25%2C%20compared%20to%2058%25%20for%20men.%20In%20urban%20areas%2C%20it%20is%2028%25%20for%20women%20compared%20to%2060%25%20for%20men%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20introduced%20a%20new%20internship%20scheme%20in%20October%202024%20to%20reduce%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20in%20the%20country.%20A%20top%20company%20needs%20to%20train%204%2C000%20people%20a%20year%20to%20achieve%20the%20target%20set%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%20Back-of-the-envelope%20calculations%20suggest%20that%20a%20private%20firm%20will%20need%20to%20spend%20Rs%2020%20crore%20every%20year%20to%20train%20youngsters.%20How%20many%20companies%20will%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20training%2C%20there%20is%20no%20guarantee%20that%20the%20trainees%20will%20be%20retained%20or%20find%20a%20job%20in%20the%20formal%20workforce.%20This%20is%20especially%20worrying%20since%20this%20scheme%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20there%20have%20been%20job%20cuts%20by%20major%20companies%20across%20the%20globe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThree%20Constructive%20Suggestions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20have%20suggested%20that%20a%20better%20way%20to%20roll%20out%20the%20scheme%20would%20have%20been%20by%20engaging%20Micro%2C%20Small%20and%20Medium%20Enterprises%20(MSMEs)%20instead%20of%20big%20firms.%20Interns%20often%20gain%20more%20practical%20experience%20in%20smaller%20firms%2C%20and%20these%20businesses%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20benefit%20from%20an%20extra%20set%20of%20hands.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20likelihood%20of%20retaining%20interns%20and%20converting%20them%20into%20medium-%20to%20long-term%20employees%20would%20be%20significantly%20higher%2C%20creating%20a%20more%20sustainable%20model%20for%20both%20interns%20and%20MSMEs.%20This%20would%20also%20encourage%20and%20ease%20the%20transition%20of%20an%20own%20account%20establishment%20(establishment%20operated%20without%20any%20hired%20employees)%20to%20a%20hired%20worker%20establishment%20(establishment%20operated%20with%20at%20least%20one%20hired%20employee)%2C%20which%20would%20benefit%20the%20economy%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20tackle%20urban%20unemployment%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20should%20accept%20what%20many%20states%20have%20done%2C%20and%20the%20parliamentary%20standing%20committee%20on%20labour%20had%20suggested%20in%20its%2025th%20report%3A%20create%20an%20employment%20guarantee%20programme%20for%20urban%20areas%20with%20special%20emphasis%20on%20women.%20States%20like%20Kerala%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20Telangana%2C%20and%20West%20Bengal%20already%20run%20similar%20schemes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20urban%20unemployment%20guarantee%20programme%20will%20be%20a%20step%20in%20line%20with%20the%20Right%20to%20Livelihood%2C%20which%20has%20been%20read%20into%20the%20Right%20to%20Life%20through%20judicial%20interpretation.%20Moreover%2C%20it%20will%20be%20a%20step%20towards%20turning%20the%20Right%20to%20Work%20(Article%2041)%2C%20currently%20a%20directive%20principle%2C%20into%20a%20fundamental%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJoyce%20Banda%2C%20former%20President%20of%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20poorest%20countries%2C%20Malawi%2C%20put%20it%20well%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20seeds%20of%20success%20in%20every%20nation%20on%20earth%20are%20best%20planted%20in%20women%20and%20children%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EResearch%20credit%3A%20Dheemunt%20Jain%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Derek%20O'Brien%2C%20MP%2C%20leads%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730693100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2F6sk97jm8_unemployment_625x300_04_November_24.jpg%2