ed%20on%20the%20impulse%20to%20leave%20the%20classroom%20when%20I%20was%20overwhelmed.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpsychiatrist-kids-tips-minimizing-childrens-screen-time-smartphone-laptop-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eworked%20closely%20with%20his%20psychiatrist%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20We%20needed%20to%20help%20my%20son%20find%20stability%20and%20support%20his%20brain%20chemistry%20so%20he%20could%20regulate%20his%20emotions%2C%20make%20friends%2C%20and%20stay%20in%20class.%20He%20was%20officially%20diagnosed%20with%20autism%20and%20ADHD%20at%20age%206.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThen%20the%20doctor%20offered%20to%20evaluate%20me.%20At%20first%2C%20I%20said%20no.%20As%20a%20single%20working%20mother%20of%20three%2C%20holding%20a%20successful%20long-term%20job%20in%20education%20and%20the%20arts%2C%20I%20saw%20myself%20as%20calm%20and%20fairly%20relaxed.%20But%20then%20figured%2C%20why%20not%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20perspective%20shifted%20after%20the%20psychiatrist%20completed%20the%20evaluation%20and%20informed%20me%20that%20I%20have%20both%20ADHD%20and%20autism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC10177627%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20A%20study%20from%202022%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3Eshows%20that%20ADHD%20can%20cooccur%20in%20approximately%2040%25%20to%2070%25%20of%20people%20with%20a%20diagnosis%20of%20autism%2C%20and%20both%20run%20in%20families%3Cspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20explained%20that%20hyperactivity%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20in%20late-diagnosed%20women%20like%20me%20%E2%80%94%20can%20happen%20internally.%20It%20manifested%20in%20my%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-productivity-exec-how-to-be-efficient-at-work-office-2024-4%5C%22%20target