%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDixie%20La%20Pierre%20is%20a%2055-year-old%20who%20remembers%20what%20it%20was%20like%20to%20grow%20up%20poor%20in%20New%20Orleans.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20she%20was%2010%2C%20her%20class%20was%20having%20a%20McDonald's%20that%20she%20knew%20her%20mother%20couldn't%20afford.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHer%20teacher%20randomly%20selected%20her%20to%20do%20chores%20so%20she%20too%20could%20participate%20in%20the%20class%20treat.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%2C%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-parent-loneliness-no-partner-202404%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emom%20was%20a%20single%20parent%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20myself%20and%20my%20younger%20sister%20in%20New%20Orleans.%20Throughout%20my%20childhood%2C%20my%20mom%20worked%20between%20three%20and%20four%20jobs%20at%20a%20time%20to%20provide%20for%20our%20family.%20She%20worked%20for%20an%20insurance%20company%2C%20a%20jeweler%2C%20and%20a%20hotel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20didn't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-get-medical-bills-reduced-negotiate-challenge-payment-plan-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equalify%20for%20health%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20she%20had%20to%20make%20sure%20she%20was%20earning%20enough%20to%20pay%20for%20health%20visits%20to%20the%20doctor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20her%20long%20hours%20at%20work%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillionaires-billionaires-who-came-from-nothing-rags-to-riches-stories-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewe%20were%20always%20poor%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20remember%20mom%20telling%20us%20to%20only%20use%20our%20asthma%20pumps%20if%20our%20lips%20were%20going%20blue%20because%20she%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20keep%20buying%20new%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22575594bf-4cce-49cb-997b-60d5eddf7a7e%5C%22%3EMy%20mom%20had%20to%20work%20long%20hours%20to%20send%20us%20to%20school%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20late%2070s%2C%20New%20Orleans%20teachers%20went%20on%20strike.%20No%20one%20knew%20how%20long%20they%20would%20last%20but%20there%20were%20rumors%20it%20could%20go%20on%20for%20a%20year.%20My%20mom%20was%20petrified%20how%20our%20education%20would%20be%20impacted%20by%20the%20strike%2C%20so%20she%20asked%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreta-gerwig-says-her-catholic-upbringing-influenced-barbie-scenes-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elocal%20Catholic%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20my%20sister%20and%20I%20could%20attend%20at%20a%20reduced%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20worked%20out%20a%20deal%20that%20my%20mom%20would%20only%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20one%20child's%20tuition%20and%20the%20other%20could%20attend%20for%20free.%20The%20nuns%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fschool-uniforms-around-the-world-2017-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprovided%20us%20with%20our%20uniform%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20free%2C%20and%20we%20had%20free%20breakfast%20and%20lunch%20at%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20paying%20for%20school%20meant%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-mom-two-jobs-burned-out-no-work-life-balance-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emom%20had%20to%20work%20even%20longer%20hours%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20often%20didn't%20see%20her.%20She'd%20work%20late%20into%20the%20night%20and%20leave%20early%20in%20the%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20still%2C%20we%20often%20didn't%20have%20money%20for%20groceries.%20Our%20electricity%20and%20water%20were%20cut%20off%20at%20points.%20I%20effectively%20was%20my%20sister's%20carer%2C%20making%20sure%20we%20both%20got%20home%20safely%20after%20school%2C%20did%20our%20homework%2C%20ate%2C%20and%20got%20ready%20for%20school%20the%20next%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2259adf685-9aa1-4336-8f46-6744aeaca2c7%5C%22%3EWe%20couldn't%20afford%20field%20trips%20or%20special%20events%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnytime%20there%20was%20a%20school%20field%20trip%20or%20special%20event%2C%20I%20didn't%20even%20bother%20to%20ask%20my%20mom.%20I%20knew%20we%20couldn't%20afford%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhenever%20I%20had%20to%20miss%20something%20or%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20pay%20for%20a%20money%20request%20in%20school%2C%20I%20learned%20the%20best%20thing%20to%20do%20is%20just%20to%20look%20down%20at%20your%20shoes%20or%20hands%20so%20you%20can't%20see%20when%20people%20are%20staring%20at%20you.%20I%20was%20just%20resigned%20that%20this%20was%20how%20it%20would%20go.%20I%20would%20never%20be%20able%20to%20do%20what%20the%20other%20children%20could%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20once%2C%20my%204%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%20grade%20teacher%20gave%20everyone%20in%20my%20class%20a%20photocopied%20menu%20from%20McDonald's.%20We%20were%20told%20to%20take%20it%20home%2C%20choose%20what%20we%20wanted%2C%20and%20bring%20our%20order%20back%20in%20with%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20day%2C%20I%20brought%20in%20my%20packed%20lunch%2C%20knowing%20it%20was%20McDonald's%20day.%20If%20anyone%20asked%2C%20I%20would%20just%20say%20I%20forgot%20it%20was%20McDonald's%20day.%20Everyone%20except%20for%20me%20brought%20their%20order%20and%20money%20in.%20Like%20always%2C%20I%20just%20looked%20down%2C%20avoiding%20stares.%20If%20I%20was%20quiet%20about%20it%2C%20hopefully%20no%20one%20would%20notice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b746d8ed-341e-464f-953a-ab0fd7597156%5C%22%3EMy%20teacher%20'randomly'%20selected%20me%20to%20earn%20money%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20homeroom%20class%2C%20my%20teacher%20asked%20the%20class%20who%20would%20like%20to%20earn%20some%20extra%20money%20for%20McDonald's.%20Everyone%20raised%20their%20hands%2C%20including%20me.%20He%20closed%20his%20eyes%2C%20spun%20around%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Brandomly%26quot%3B%20pointed%20at%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20did%20the%20chores%2C%20and%20he%20took%20some%20money%20out%20of%20his%20wallet%20and%20put%20it%20into%20the%20c