s%20for%20the%20products%20on%20this%20page%20are%20from%20partners%20that%20compensate%20us%20and%20terms%20apply%20to%20offers%20listed%20(see%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Four-partners%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvertiser%20disclosure%20with%20our%20list%20of%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20details).%20However%2C%20our%20opinions%20are%20our%20own.%20See%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpersonal-finance-editorial-standards%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20products%20and%20services%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20you%20make%20smart%20decisions%20with%20your%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22relationship%20couple%20friends%20toxic%20argument%20sad%20upset%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6725490b01ea6d83dee5c080%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221060%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20reader%20is%20not%20pictured.%3Cp%3EDrazen_%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFor%20Love%20%26amp%3B%20Money%20is%20a%20weekly%20Business%20Insider%20column%20answering%20relationship%20and%20money%20questions.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThis%20week%2C%20a%20reader%20disagrees%20with%20their%20%3Cstrong%3Efianc%C3%A9e%20on%20whether%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20or%20rent.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EOur%20columnist%20says%20it's%20important%20to%20discuss%20the%20underlying%20reasons%20each%20partner%20wants%20what%20they%20want.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EGot%20a%20question%20for%20our%20columnist%3F%20Write%20to%20For%20Love%20%26amp%3B%20Money%20using%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSdhFnAxR57cNtGiwNUd-6vLAYAc75grvly3C10-854vFP4arw%2Fviewform%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethis%20Google%20form%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDear%20For%20Love%20%26amp%3B%20Money%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20fianc%C3%A9e%20and%20I%20disagree%20on%20buying%20a%20house%20versus%20renting.%20I%20say%20buying%20a%20home%20is%20an%20investment%2C%20while%20she%20says%20it's%20a%20major%20financial%20burden.%20Who's%20right%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESincerely%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAt%20Odds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDear%20At%20Odds%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20and%20your%20fianc%C3%A9e%20disagree%20on%20something%20that%20has%20become%20a%20popular%20topic%20of%20debate%20in%20recent%20years.%20For%20decades%2C%20getting%20on%20the%20property%20ladder%C2%A0and%20having%20a%20house%20with%20a%20picket%20fence%20was%20central%20to%20the%20American%20dream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20has%20become%20financially%20unfeasible%20for%20many%20people%2C%20and%20the%20social%20expectation%20of%20home%20ownership%20is%20far%20less%20definitive.%20While%20experts%20have%20and%20will%20continue%20debating%20what%20the%20average%20person%20should%20do%2C%20the%20truth%20is%20that%20whether%20home%20ownership%20or%20renting%20is%20better%20depends%20on%20the%20individual.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuying%20was%20the%20better%20option%20for%20me%20and%20my%20family%20because%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fbest-mortgage-lenders%5C%22%3Emortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%20payment%20is%20significantly%20lower%20than%20renting%20for%20a%20family%20our%20size%20in%20our%20town.%20We%20also%20received%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20the%20down%20payment%20on%20our%20first%20home%20from%20my%20husband's%20grandmother%20%E2%80%94%20a%20financial%20gift%20contingent%20on%20purchasing%20a%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20excited%20about%20painting%20a%20house%2C%20knocking%20down%20walls%2C%20and%20adding%20bathrooms%2C%20and%20that%20desire%20outweighed%20the%20burden%20of%20not%20having%20a%20landlord%20to%20assist%20us%20with%20the%20cost%20of%20repairs.%20Buying%20has%20paid%20off%20for%20us.%20When%20it%20was%20time%20to%20sell%2C%20the%20value%20of%20our%20first%20house%20doubled%2C%20putting%20us%20in%20a%20great%20position%20to%20buy%20our%20current%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20some%20people%20would%20see%20the%20money%20and%20time%20we've%20poured%20into%20landscaping%20and%20repairs%20as%20not%20worth%20it%20at%20any%20price.%20This%20is%20why%2C%20ultimately%2C%20it%20depends%20on%20your%20particular%20circumstances.%20Where%20you%20live%2C%20the%20makeup%20of%20your%20income%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%3Esavings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20your%20long-term%20goals%2C%20and%20what%20success%20means%20to%20you%20are%20all%20factors%20worth%20considering.%20You%20don't%20need%20an%20official%20ruling%20from%20an%20external%20source%20to%20tell%20you%20it's%20right%20or%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20external%20sources%20can%20provide%20guidance%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20high-stakes%20decisions.%20So%2C%20to%20understand%20what%20that%20external%20ruling%20might%20be%2C%20I%20contacted%20certified%20financial%20planner%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnemesrush.com%2Fabout%2Fteam%2Fjustin-rush%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJustin%20Rush%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Rush%20also%20said%20it%20comes%20down%20to%20the%20individual%2C%20because%20either%20option%20has%20benefits%20and%20costs.%20Rush%20pointed%20out%20that%20renting%20offers%20flexibility%2C%20but%20home%20ownership%20offers%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20landlord%20means%20someone%20else%20will%20take%20care%20of%20your%20repairs%2C%20but%20that%20same%20person%20can%20choose%20to%20raise%20your%20rent.%20Buying%20a%20home%20is%20a%20strategy%20for%20building%20wealth%2C%20but%20you%20must%20also%20factor%20in%20the%20significant%20cost%20of%20home%20maintenance%20over%20the%20years.%20Your%20roof%20and%20driveway%20will%20need%20to%20be%20repaired%20or%20replaced%20now%20and%20then.%20Rush%20says%20that%20the%20value%20of%20a%20home%20often%20appreciates%20%E2%80%94%20but%20sometimes%20they%20depreciate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20assumes%20you%20can%20afford%20the%20steep%20upfront%20costs%20of%20moving%20from%20renting%20to%20buying.%20Rush%20suggested%20looking%20into%20smaller%20banks%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwhat-is-credit-union%5C%22%3Ecredit%20unions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20often%20offer%20great%20incentives%20for%20first-time%20home%20buyers%2C%20and%20researching%20other%20programs%20designed%20to%20help%20people%20get%20on%20the%20property%20ladder%20to%20help%20with%20the%20transition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20let's%20say%20you%20look%20at%20the%20numbers%20and%20find%20it%20is%20cheaper%20to%20buy%20than%20rent%20in%20your%20area%2C%20and%20you'll%20have%20it%20paid%20off%20when%20you're%20ready%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fretirement%5C%22%3Eretirement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Better%20still%2C%20you%20find%20a%20credit%20union%20offering%20an%20incredible%20incentive%20that%20allows%20you%20to%20get%20started%20without%20making%20an%20enormous%20down%20payment.%20So%2C%20you%20take%20this%20winning%20case%20and%20present%20it%20to%20your%20fianc%C3%A9e.%20You're%20right.%20She's%20wrong.%20You've%20proven%20that%20buying%20is%20the%20smarter%20option%20for%20you%20both.%20None%20of%20this%20means%20your%20fianc%C3%A9e%20will%20automatically%20concede%20the%20point%20because%20these%20big%20life%20choices%20are%20rarely%20as%20simple%20as%20a%20few%20winning%20data%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnderneath%20the%20questions%20of%20dollar%20signs%20and%20right%20or%20wrong%20are%20softer%20but%20no%20less%20important%20factors%20%E2%80%94%20like%20watching%20your%20parents%20turn%20down%20incredible%20job%20opportunities%20because%20they%20have%20a%20mortgage%20to%20consider%2C%20private%20fantasies%20of%20giving%20it%20all%20up%20for%20an%20RV%20and%20the%20open%20road%2C%20or%20lying%20awake%20at%20night%20spinning%20about%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20worth%20of%20debt%20on%20your%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20goes%20both%20ways%2C%20however.%20Maybe%20you%20were%20kicked%20out%20of%20a%20childhood%20home%20because%20your%20landlord%20died%20and%20their%20kids%20wanted%20to%20sell.%20Maybe%20when%20you%20close%20your%20eyes%20and%20dream%20big%2C%20you%20see%20a%20large%20house%20in%20the%20countryside%20crawling%20with%20children%20and%20dogs.%20Or%20maybe%20you%20lay%20awake%20at%20night%20worrying%20that%20you%20haven't%20invested%20or%20saved%20enough%2C%20and%20buying%20a%20house%20will%20put%20you%20at%20ease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20and%20your%20fianc%C3%A9e%20must%20be%20open%20with%20one%20another%20about%20what's%20going%20on%20beneath%20this%20difference%20of%20opinion%20because%20those%20softer%20considerations%20will%20guide%20you%20toward%20compromises%20that%20will%20genuinely%20work%20for%20both%20of%20you.%20This%20could%20mean%20agreeing%20to%20rent%2C%20save%2C%20and%20begin%20your%20house%20hunt%20in%202030.%20It%20could%20mean%20not%20buying%20a%20house%20unless%20it%20meets%20specific%20conditions.%20Maybe%20the%20answer%20is%20buying%20a%20home%20%E2%80%94%20but%20committing%20to%20selling%20it%20should%20any%20great%20life%20opportunities%20arise.%20Or%20perhaps%20renting%20forever%20but%20finding%20other%20ways%20to%20invest%20and%20put%20down%20roots%20is%20the%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20in%20any%20difference%20of%20opinion%20with%20a%20loved%20one%2C%20the%20key%20is%20figuring%20out%20what%20works%20for%20you%20both.%20This%20means%20concession%20and%20compromise%20and%20not%20getting%20stuck%20on%20who's%20right%20and%20who's%20wrong.%20You'r