%20headshot%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671fa4bb9b3250dbbcea7e87%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAuthor%20Rebecca%20Chamaa.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Rebecca%20Chamaa%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI'd%20like%20to%20pay%20off%20my%20mortgage%20before%20my%20husband%20retires.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMortgage%20rates%20are%20expected%20to%20fall%20after%20the%20Fed%20cut%20interest%20rates%2C%20which%20could%20affect%20our%20plans.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBut%20after%20doing%20the%20math%20again%2C%20we're%20still%20keeping%20money%20in%20a%20CD%20instead.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20I%20bought%20my%20first%20house%20in%20my%2020s%2C%20that%20was%20the%20only%20financial%20planning%20I%20did%20until%20well%20into%20my%2030s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20didn't%20make%20much%20money%20in%20the%20first%20decade%20of%20our%20marriage%2C%20so%20there%20wasn't%20a%20lot%20of%20extra%20cash%20to%20plan%20with.%20Luckily%2C%20one%20thing%20we%20have%20always%20had%20going%20for%20us%20as%20a%20couple%20is%20that%20we%20are%20both%20frugal%20and%20will%20go%20out%20of%20our%20way%20to%20save%20even%20%245.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20change%20we've%20made%20from%20our%20former%20approach%20to%20money%20is%20watching%20and%20reading%20about%20interest%20rates.%20Now%20that%20I'm%20paying%20attention%2C%20we%20can%20make%20decisions%20that%20impact%20our%20bottom%20line%2C%20even%20if%20they%20take%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20research%20and%20effort%20on%20our%20part.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20we%20considered%20moving%20part%20of%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%3Eemergency%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20portion%20of%20other%20investments%20to%20pay%20off%20our%20mortgage%2C%20a%20dream%20I%20wanted%20to%20realize%20before%20my%20husband%20gave%20up%20his%20full-time%20job%20and%20moved%20into%20partial%20retirement.%20Not%20having%20a%20mortgage%20in%20retirement%20would%20make%20a%20significant%20difference%20in%20our%20monthly%20financial%20obligations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20we%20ran%20the%20numbers%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20wait.%20The%20interest%20we%20would%20pay%20on%20the%20loan%20was%20less%20than%20the%20interest%20we%20would%20receive%20if%20we%20took%20that%20money%20and%20deposited%20it%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-1-year-cd-rates%5C%22%3Eone-year%20certificate%20of%20deposit%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20we%20would%20make%20a%20net%20gain%20of%20about%20%2460%20a%20month.%20That%20used%20to%20be%20enough%20for%20a%20week's%20worth%20of%20groceries%2C%20but%20now%2C%20thanks%20to%20inflation%2C%20pays%20for%20about%20half%20of%20a%20week's%20grocery%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Fed%20cut%20rates%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20years%20during%20its%20September%20meeting%20and%20with%20talk%20of%20a%20further%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwill-mortgage-rates-go-down-this-year%5C%22%3Edecline%20in%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20coming%20year%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20rerun%20the%20numbers%20and%20see%20if%20we%20should%20move%20some%20money%20around%20and%20pay%20off%20that%20mortgage.%20We%20are%20even%20closer%20to%20my%20husband%20going%20from%20a%209-to-5%20to%20a%20more%20part-time%20gig%2C%20so%20is%20now%20the%20time%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20did%20the%20math%20on%20opening%20a%20CD%20instead%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20refinanced%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2F30-year-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3E30-year%20mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20a%2015-year%20mortgage%20in%202020.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20we%20were%20able%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwhen-to-refinance-mortgage%5C%22%3Erefinance%20our%20mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%202.5%25%20interest.%20I%20know%20how%20low%20that%20sounds%20today%2C%20and%20that's%20the%20reason%20that%20the%20higher%20interest%20rates%20paid%20on%20cash%20deposits%20at%20banks%20have%20kept%20us%20from%20moving%20money%20to%20pay%20off%20our%20mortgage.%20It%20simply%20didn't%20make%20financial%20sense%20to%20do%20so%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20still%20doesn't%2C%20at%20least%20not%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20simplify%20it%2C%20let's%20say%20we%20have%20%24150%2C000%20left%20on%20our%20mortgage%20and%2011%20years%20left%20on%20those%20payments.%20That%20means%20we%20are%20paying%20about%20%24270%20a%20month%20in%20interest%20toward%20our%20home.%20If%20we%20deposited%20%24150%2C000%20in%20a%20one-year%20CD%20available%20at%20my%20local%20bank%20at%204.83%25%20APY%2C%20we%20would%20make%20roughly%20%24590%20in%20the%20first%20month%20of%20interest.%20That%20is%20a%20positive%20gain%20of%20%24320%2C%20which%20would%20pay%20for%20over%20half%20of%20our%20monthly%20grocery%20bill.%20With%20the%20recent%20price%20increases%20in%20almost%20everything%2C%20that%20is%20no%20small%20dent%20in%20our%20monthly%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20searched%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwho-has-the-best-cd-rates-right-now%5C%22%3Ebest%20CD%20rates%20right%20now%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20found%20the%20higher%20range%20to%20be%20between%203.75%25%20and%204.8%25.%20So%2C%20my%20local%20bank%20is%20still%20offering%20a%20slightly%20higher%20rate%20than%20many%20others%2C%20but%20what%20stood%20out%20from%20last%20year%20is%20that%20rather%20than%20providing%2012-month%20CDs%2C%20most%20banks%20only%20give%20these%20higher%20rates%20on%203-month%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-6-month-cd-rates%5C%22%3E6-month%20CDs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20scenario%20makes%20perfect%20sense%2C%20considering%20the%20talk%20of%20multiple%20rate%20cuts.%20These%20banks%20don't%20want%20to%20lock%20in%20an%20interest%20rate%20that%20they%20would%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20an%20extended%20period%20after%20the%20rates%20have%20gone%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-no-penalty-cds%5C%22%3Ebest%20no-penalty%20CDs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20a%20good%20way%20to%20lock%20in%20higher%20rates%20on%20CDs%20without%20facing%20penalties%20if%20you%20need%20to%20withdraw%20funds%20before%20the%20maturity%20date.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fcit-bank-cd-rates%5C%22%3ECIT%20Bank%20CD%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fraisin-review%5C%22%3ERaisin%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20popular%20no-penalty%20CD%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20still%20don't%20plan%20to%20pay%20off%20our%20mortgage%20early%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPaying%20off%20our%20mortgage%20early%20still%20doesn't%20make%20financial%20sense.%20Interest%20rates%20would%20have%20to%20go%20down%20several%20points%20for%20us%20to%20make%20more%20money%20paying%20off%20our%20mortgage%20than%20when%20we%20invest%20the%20money%20in%20other%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20it%20doesn't%20make%20sense%20to%20do%20this%20now%20...%20but%20if%20interest%20rates%20return%20to%20where%20they%20were%20in%202020%20(not%20likely%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20the%20lowest%20rates%20in%20four%20decades%20were%20in%20response%20to%20the%20pandemic)%20it%20would%20be%20worth%20considering%20again.%20Even%20if%20the%20rates%20don't%20go%20down%20to%202020%20levels%2C%20it%20may%20eventually%20make%20sense%20to%20revisit%20our%20numbers%20and%20head%20into%20retirement%20mortgage-free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20mortgage-free%20would%20give%20us%20more%20flexibility%20in%20our%20monthly%